Class Summary
AbstractPlot  
DrawFunction Abstract base class for drawing functions onto the PlotPanel subclasses.
DrawHistApplet Create an instance of Histogram, add a Gaussian generated distribution of data to it and display it.
DrawLine Drawing straight line onto the PlotPanel.
DrawPoints Drawing points on the PlotPanel.
HistErrPanel Display the histogram data.
Histogram This class provides the bare essentials for a histogram.
HistogramAdaptR1 This class provides provides histograms that offer the option to adapt the range to keep all points within bin limits.
HistogramStat This class provides provides additional statistical measures of the histogram distribution.
HistogramStatR1 This class comes from a refactoring of Histogram, HistogramStats, HistogramAdapt, and HistogramMedian.
HistPanel Display histogram data on a PlotPanel subclass.
HistStatsApplet This program will run as an applet inside an application frame.
PlotFormat This class provides a static method getFormatted that returns a double value as a string in decimal or scientific notation.
PlotPanel This abstract class extends JPanel and provides methods to display a plot of data points, a histogram, etc.
RanDistGaussianApplet This program will run as an applet inside an application frame.
RanDistTransformApplet This program will run as an applet inside an application frame.

The applet uses the HistPanel to display contents of an instance of Histogram.
UIDrawHistApplet This program will run as an applet inside an application frame.
